<HEADLINE>
FT  11 SEP 92 / International Capital Markets: John Govett launches funds
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TRACY CORRIGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
JOHN GOVETT Unit Management has launched four authorised futures funds,
adding to the limited range of UK unit trusts investing in derivative
instruments.
The Securities and Investments Board opened the door to unit trusts
investing in derivative instruments more than a year ago, but only two
companies, John Govett and Legal &amp; General, have so far taken advantage of
the new regulations, which many market participants have criticised as too
restrictive.
Up to 10 per cent of the assets of futures and options funds (Fofs) can be
invested in derivative products, while the riskier geared futures and
options funds (GFofs) can have up to 20 per cent of their assets in futures
and options.
ED&amp;F Mann has raised Dollars 220m in year to end July, in joint venture
futures funds in various countries, including non-unit trust futures funds
in the UK, in conjunction with Providence Capital.
</TEXT>
