FT  11 SEP 92 / Council decision
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
NORTH Tyneside council decided last night to seek recovery of enhanced
redundancy payments made to 396 of its former employees.
Last night's decision follows a High Court ruling that North Tyneside's
enhanced severance scheme was unlawful. Of Pounds 2.54m in payments made
under the scheme in 1990-91, Pounds 1.81m was made without specific
statutory authority, the court was told.
