FT  11 SEP 92 / Australians giving up search for work
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By EMILIA TAGAZA
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CANBERRA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
MORE unemployed Australians are giving up the search for work. Figures
released by the government yesterday show that the proportion of the work
force actively seeking work fell 0.3 percentage points to 63.2 per cent in
August, Emilia Tagaza writes from Canberra.
This fall pulled the unemployment rate slightly down to 10.9 per cent last
month from 11 per cent in July. This was the 12th consecutive month
Australia's unemployment rate had exceeded 10 per cent.
